nodes.title: Important!!
widgets_values:
If ReActor does not work, it's highly possible that you are installing ReActor incorrectly.

See: https://github.com/kinelite/kinelite-repo

on how to install ReActor correctly. You must follow the instruction RELIGIOUSLY.

nodes.title: Important!!
widgets_values: If the face got swapped on the wrong person, change input_faces_order in ReActor Options node to specify which face the model should swap.

nodes.title: Tips
widgets_values: Change context_expand_factor to specify how large the image should be cropped. (larger for more context, but less resolution.)

nodes.title: Tips
widgets_values: This parameter will fix the height at 1024. The maximum width or height of any loaded image should NOT be larger than 16384

nodes.title: Tips
widgets_values:
Image Strength

Highest = keep the tone color of subject
High = tone color fits better
Medium = like High, sometimes better

nodes.title: Tips
widgets_values:
if you encounter ImageConcatenate error about dimension,

Set match_image_size = true.

nodes.title: Tips
widgets_values: If this node got error, try reloading ComfyUI and other workflows first. If the problem persists, you can bypass it or just remove it entirely.

nodes.title: Tips
widgets_values:
if you encounter ImageConcatenate error about dimension,

Set match_image_size = true.

nodes.title: Load face if it's a person
Tips
widgets_values: Try changing image_strength in the StyleModelApplySimple node.

nodes.title: Load destination (right-click to mask the area)
Tips
widgets_values:
Disable Face Swap Unit if you don't want to swap face, e.g., transfering non-human or encountering errors about ReActor nodes.

Enable Upscaler when you are ready because it has a long render time.
